  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>1.17.14 is a minor update including some small features and bug fixes.</p><p>Scheduled 11:30 CT on October 26, 2020</p><h3 id=\"id-1.17.14-Improvements\">Improvements</h3><p>We\u2019ve upgraded the following list views in RepairQ, allowing users to customize which columns appear on these pages and save custom views for you or your team to use.</p><ul><li><p>Inventory Transfers</p></li><li><p>RMA Batches</p></li><li><p>Invoices</p></li></ul><p><br/>List View Exports - In a List View, you can add or remove columns. However, until now, when you exported a list, the export file only contained a pre-defined set of columns. The exported list did not reflect the view you created on screen.\u00a0Now, when you export a list, the export file will contain the columns that you set on screen. This feature is useful for exporting lists/data related to catalog, tickets, inventory and allows you to use List Views for reporting.</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
